sql:
SELECT SUM(revenue) AS total_revenue
FROM roi
WHERE campaign_id = '0';

SELECT campaign_id, SUM(revenue) AS total_revenue, SUM(profit) AS total_profit
FROM roi
GROUP BY campaign_id;

external_knowledge:
- "reaped a harvest" refers to campaigns with a positive average daily ROI;
- "sparked at least one flame" means campaigns with at least one click;
- "sparked at least one bloom" means campaigns with at least one conversion;
- "the richness of their fruit" refers to the average daily ROI of the campaigns.
